metadata.name: FXHash 2.0 Card #173
metadata.description:
Join the Xtra Card adventure on fx(hash) with our first-ever free NFT collectionon Tezos! This groundbreaking series marks a significant transition for Xtra Card, blending generative art with interactive elements, in celebration of the launch of fx(hash) 2.0.

### Interact

S: Save your card as a PNG.
R: Toggle automatic rotation On/Off.
M: Switch the mirror effect.
P: Show or hide particles.
L: Turn lines between particles On/Off.

### Categories, Probabilities, and Total Iterations

Gold (Gold): Ultra-rare, only 5% chance - approximately 26 cards out of 512.
Silver (Silver): Exceptional, with a 33% chance - around 169 cards.
Bronze: The majority of the collection with the remaining probability - about 317 cards.
Every card draw is unique, with defined probabilities for each category. Features such as metal type, card number, and particle style are randomly determined, adding variety and excitement to each mint.

### Unique Features
Xtra Card's collection offers distinctive characteristics:

Metal: The metal of the card (Gold, Silver, or Bronze).
Card Number: A unique identifier for each card.
Particle Type: Different styles to customize the ambiance of your card.

###
Animated / Interactive / Prerendered components
Made with P5js

metadata.name: Ryokou #350
metadata.description:
Ryokou, the Japanese term for travel, marks the commencement of every journey, much like the initiation of this algorithm. I initially conceived this idea in "Tessera" and have since extended and incorporated it into various other artistic endeavors.

The canvas is versatile, offering over 40 color themes and even more potential combinations.

Press s in live mode for a PNG download
Press (1-5) to change resolution

Lammetje December 2023

metadata.name: Slumbers #198
metadata.description:
Generative abstract artwork that explores forms, shapes, coloring and brushwork.

Options:

- press 'f' to turn off paper-like texture (recommended for print on hi-quality paper)
- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Colors and textures might differ slightly on some devices due to the heavy use of low alpha blending. Calibrated and tested on Firefox 107.0 & Chrome 107.0.5304.107 on Win10 x64 Intel machine.

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, November, 2022.
tags: slumbers volatile moods abstract generative painting colors brushwork

metadata.name: Unsolicited abstraction of modern times #223
metadata.description:
This piece is an abstraction and a reflection on the last era, on all that we have built and become. Are we proud of it or has it just been the result of iterating through the days? Since the technology boom, we have experienced great improvements, but perhaps also massive ...mistakes?‚Ä®‚Ä®

Inspired by textbooks of the 80s, with elements that remind us of industry, technology, networks and systems, "Unsolicited abstraction of modern times" invites us to question our work to date. Has everything really changed?

unknowable 2022




Usage:
press [s] - save pixels (png)
press [p] - save vectors (svg)

Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-ND 4.0)

metadata.name: QuadTubes - Abstract Variations #195
metadata.description:
This piece features abstract patterns created using an algorithm I call QuadTubes.

It works by continuously stroking a set of quadratic curves that run through a set of points while rotating those points along a constant orbit.

This piece features 13 different arrangements and 11 different colors sets, so there should be around 20 pieces of each arrangement. Check the variations function to preview the different arrangements and styles.

The piece will slowly render and automatically pause after reaching its final form. You can press Space to Pause/Unpause the piece and let it run longer resulting in more saturated colors.

You can adjust the rendering speed with up/down-arrows or you can also load the page with
'&Speed=*'
at the end of the url to adjust the rendering speed (default = 25) and press S at any time to save an image of any state of the animation.
 
Initial minters will receive 10% royalties.


PLEASE NOTE: 
This piece was developed in and is best viewed in Chrome (100.0.4896.127). Moreover hardware acceleration needs to be enabled in the browser settings. There are still some browsers & devices that struggle with this piece, most notably iOS and Firefox. There is a fallback which is enabled in Firefox and iOS by default that works without hardware acceleration but produces notably different results in texture and color saturation (especially on iOS). You may force the fallback by appending "&noHA=true" to the url in live view and force the original rendering by appending "&forceHA=true" (Note you can combine multiple URL parameters with an "&", eg "www.fxhash.xyz[...]?Speed=50&forceHA=true").
 Please make sure that you have a device and browser capable of rendering this piece before minting.

metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #533
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.

metadata.name: Ordinary Places #103
metadata.description:
‚ÄúOrdinary Places‚Äù is a fully-coded meditation on the poetic beauty of everyday landscapes. 

The architectural characters in these landscapes include water towers (inspired by Bernd & Hilla Becher‚Äôs ‚ÄúWater Tower‚Äù photography series), gas stations (inspired by Ed Ruscha‚Äôs ‚Äú26 Gasoline Stations‚Äù photography book), and barns (inspired by childhood memories on my grandfather‚Äôs farm). 

Yet, while these scenes may seem ordinary upon first glance, something darker lurks beneath the surface. The hidden secrets of these Ordinary Places can only be revealed through the minting process. In this sense, the outputs are not merely a collection individual scenes, but instead, a coherent world animated by shared themes and narratives.     

Pressing the down arrow saves the coded output as a .png image.

metadata.name: The complexity of the city #41
metadata.description:
Generative image from the combination of 30 blocks of buildings that vary position, scale and opacity.
All the blocks come from pictures of my own of Rio de Janeiro, S√£o Paulo and New York.
In the same line as the previous NFT¬¥s, this work explores the complexity of human constructs. 
  
Images with more density of buildings may take some time for loading. 
To save as a high-quality image (3000 x 3000 px), click "open" and press J for jpg or P for png.

Code made in P5js by Diego de los Campos under NFT License 2.0

metadata.name: Gray Copper Swallow #83
metadata.description:
"Gray Copper Swallow" is a p5.js project where isometric shapes are placed and have their size and color adjusted based on an underlying grid of shapes and colors. Each form is derived from the lightness or darkness of a particular pixel in the underlying grid. Many renders remind me of cityscapes with buildings, roads, and bridges.

Press s to save the image.
